{{BLPrefimprove|date=September 2011}}'''Alice Patten''' (born 1980) is an English actress, and the daughter of [[Chris Patten]], a prominent British Conservative politician and the last governor of [[Hong Kong]]. She has played a key role in the [[Hindi cinema|Hindi]] film ''[[Rang De Basanti]]'' (2006). She played Sue, a young British woman who comes to India to make a documentary film about the [[British rule]] in the Indian subcontinent.
Her first major role after graduation was Eugenie in ''[[Vincent in Brixton]]'' in the [[West end theatre|West End]].<ref>Cassandra Jardine, [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/4728388/Eastern-princess-turns-West-End-girl.html Eastern princess turns West End girl], ''[[Daily Telegraph]]'', 29 July 2002</ref>
In 2005 and 2006, she appeared in [[English Touring Theatre]]'s ''[[Hamlet]]'', playing [[Ophelia]] opposite [[Ed Stoppard]]âs Prince of Denmark.
In 2006, she appeared in the Hindi film ''[[Rang De Basanti]]'' as Sue McKinley. In 2008, she played Thea in ''Hedda'', a new version of Ibsen's ''[[Hedda Gabler]]'', at London's Gate Theatre and, in 2009, she guest starred as [[King Arthur|Arthur]]'s mother [[Igraine|Ygraine]] in the [[BBC]] fantasy drama series ''[[Merlin (TV series)|Merlin]]''.
Patten was educated at [[Island School]] in [[Hong Kong]] and at [[Queens' College, Cambridge|Queensâ College]], [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]].
